        <h2>Features to Look for in a Safe Instagram Unfollow Tracker</h2>

        <p>Before choosing any tool, ask yourself these questions:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Does it require your Instagram password?</strong> — Any tool asking for your login is a red flag.</li>
          <li><strong>Does it scrape data directly from Instagram?</strong> — Data scraping violates Instagram's ToS and risks your account.</li>
          <li><strong>Does it have a clear privacy policy?</strong> — Legitimate tools are transparent about data handling.</li>
          <li><strong>Are there reports of account bans?</strong> — Check reviews before signing up.</li>
          <li><strong>Is there a free trial?</strong> — Trusted tools let you try before you pay.</li>
          <li><strong>Does it support multiple profiles?</strong> — Important if you manage several accounts.</li>
          <li><strong>Is it End-to-End encrypted?</strong> — Your data should never be shared with third parties.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Safely Track Instagram Unfollowers</h2>

        <p>The safest method is to use a tool that reads your own Instagram data export — not one that connects to your account or scrapes data from Instagram's servers.</p>

        <p>Here's how to do it with Unfollow Finder:</p>

        <ol>
          <li>Open Instagram → Settings → Your Activity → Download Your Information</li>
          <li>Select JSON format and request a download</li>
          <li>Instagram will email you a download link within a few hours</li>
          <li>Unzip the file and find the <code>followers_and_following</code> folder</li>
          <li>Upload <code>followers_1.json</code> and <code>following.json</code> to <a href="https://unfollowfinder.com">Unfollow Finder</a></li>
          <li>See your results instantly — no account access required</li>
        </ol>

